# GF(p) Field — public module surface
#
# Aggregates the abstract `Field` trait (documentation contract; see
# `field_trait.spl`) plus the two concrete impl modules:
#
#   * `fe25519.spl` — Curve25519 / Ed25519 field, 5×51-bit u64 limbs (extracted
#     verbatim from `src/os/crypto/curve25519.spl` per R-C field_design.md §1).
#   * `fe_p256.spl` — NIST P-256 field, 4×64-bit limb skeleton. Byte-edge ops
#     only; arithmetic is `panic("fe_p256: not implemented yet — ...")` per
#     R-C Risk #1.
#
# Callers should `use std.common.math.field.fe25519.{fe_add, fe_mul, ...}`
# (or `fe_p256` analogues) directly. Each impl module hosts its own
# concrete `Fe25519` / `FeP256` struct because Simple's trait system does
# not yet support associated types (see `field_trait.spl` rationale).
#
# Boundary with R-B (bignum, parallel track):
#     R-B owns scalar arithmetic `Fixed<N>` under
#     `src/lib/common/math/bignum/`. R-C / I-4 owns field-native limb shapes
#     here. The two backends today (5×51 LE, 4×64 BE) both load/store bytes
#     via raw bit shifts and do **not** require a `Fixed<256>` import. If a
#     future field impl needs scalar arithmetic at the byte edge, import from
#     R-B's `bignum` rather than redefining.
